# GitHub MCP Server URL and Configuration

## URL
The exact URL for the GitHub MCP server is: **`https://api.githubcopilot.com/mcp/`**

## Configuration Methods

The documentation describes two primary approaches for setting up the GitHub MCP server:

### 1. OAuth Authentication (Recommended)
This is the simpler option requiring no additional setup. The basic configuration looks like:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "github": {
      "url": "https://api.githubcopilot.com/mcp/"
    }
  }
}
```

As stated in the documentation: "You do not need to create a PAT or install any additional software to use the remote GitHub MCP server with OAuth."

### 2. Personal Access Token (PAT) Authentication
For organizations needing more control, you can configure it with a PAT header:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "github": {
      "url": "https://api.githubcopilot.com/mcp/",
      "requestInit": {
        "headers": {
          "Authorization": "Bearer YOUR_GITHUB_PAT"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Both configurations work across Visual Studio Code, JetBrains IDEs, Visual Studio, Xcode, and Eclipse.

